                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/22468: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-25T16:00:00-00:44"
                            >June 25, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 26—6:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>211. My telegram number 198, June 18, 5 p.m. The agreement was ratified by the
                    House yesterday and the Senate this morning. The President will probably sign it
                    tomorrow. I suggest, if the <pb facs="0395" n="383" xml:id="pg_383"/> Department
                    sees no objection, that President Roosevelt send a personal message for me to
                    deliver to President Barclay as it would be very useful both here and at
                    home.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
